### Describe the bug

1. define an `interface`:
```java
public interface GrpcInterceptor extends ServerInterceptor, Prioritized {
  Integer TRACE_INTERCEPTOR_ORDER = 10000;
  Integer ACTIVITY_INTERCEPTOR_ORDER = 9999;
}
```

2. implements the GrpcInterceptor
```java
@ApplicationScoped
@GlobalInterceptor
public class ServerInterceptors implements GrpcInterceptor {

    private final Logger logger;

    @Inject
    public ServerInterceptors(Logger logger) {
        this.logger = logger;
    }

    @Override
    public <ReqT, RespT> ServerCall.Listener<ReqT> interceptCall(ServerCall<ReqT, RespT> call, Metadata headers, ServerCallHandler<ReqT, RespT> next) {
        Context context = Context.current();

        String orgId = headers.get(ORG_ID_METADATA);
        logger.infof("orgId: %s", orgId);

        if (!StringUtils.isBlank(orgId)) {
            context = context.withValue(ORG_ID_CONTEXT, orgId);
        }
        return Contexts.interceptCall(context, call, headers, next);
    }

    @Override
    public int getPriority() {
        return 0;
    }
}

```

4. test with send a request, and the GrpcInterceptor not working


### Expected behavior

`GrpcInterceptor` class should work, can print the `orgId`

### Actual behavior

`GrpcInterceptor` class not working, no related methods are called

### How to Reproduce?

A demo that reproduces the problem, https://github.com/renyijiu/quarkus-jooq-issue-demo/tree/bugs/interceptors

